title: @NFL Extends Agreement To Play Regular-Season Games at Wembley Stadium
text:
Press Releases @NFL Extends Agreement To Play Regular-Season Games at Wembley Stadium 
The NFL has extended its agreement to play regular season games at Londons Wembley Stadium through 2020. The additional 5-year agreement reiterates the NFL’s commitment to the UK. In front of a sell out crowd of 83,986, Wembley Stadium hosted the first International Series game of 2015 in October 4th between the Miami Dolphins and the New York Jets.  //woodlawnpost.com/?p=123735   25 2015. Filed under Business
